criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:

  -  18-65 years old;

  -  Body weight >110 lbs;

  -  Hemoglobin >12.5 g/dL.

Exclusion Criteria:

  -  Ineligible for donation based on the New York Blood Center blood donor questionnaire;

  -  Systolic blood pressure >180 or <90 mm Hg, diastolic blood pressure >100 or <50 mm
     Hg;

  -  Heart rate <50 or >100;

  -  Temperature >99.5 F prior to donation;

  -  Temperature >100.4 F or subjective feeling of illness prior to transfusion (this is
     to avoid having a concurrent illness affect post-transfusion measurements);

  -  Positive results on standard blood donor infectious disease testing;

  -  Positive urine pregnancy test.
